### 8. State Machine

Define lifecycle states of the main entity and allowed transitions.

**Format:**
- List all states
- Define allowed transitions
- Specify forbidden transitions
- Map transitions to permissions

**Example:**
```markdown
## 8. State Machine: CustomerImportJob

**States:**
- QUEUED: Job accepted, waiting for execution
- PROCESSING: Job actively creating customer records
- COMPLETED: All rows processed successfully
- PARTIAL_SUCCESS: Some rows succeeded, some failed
- FAILED: Job aborted due to system error

**Allowed Transitions:**
- QUEUED → PROCESSING (when worker picks up job)
- PROCESSING → COMPLETED (all rows succeeded)
- PROCESSING → PARTIAL_SUCCESS (some rows failed)
- PROCESSING → FAILED (system error, rollback)

**Forbidden Transitions:**
- COMPLETED → any other state (immutable terminal state)
- FAILED → PROCESSING (no retry from FAILED; must create new job)

**Permission Guards:**
- Only CRM_ADMIN or job owner can view job status
- Only SYSTEM can transition job states
```

