### 13. Security Requirements

Define authentication, authorization, and security controls.

**Architecture Standards:**
- Follow spring-security.mdc
- Reference RBAC from docs/architecture/rbac-model.md
- Apply data-scope rules (ALL/TEAM/OWN)

**Example:**
```markdown
## 13. Security Requirements

### Authentication
- All endpoints require valid JWT token
- Token must contain `roles` claim

### Authorization (RBAC)
| Endpoint | Required Permission | Data Scope |
|---|---|---|
| POST /import/upload | customer:create | N/A (upload accessible to role holder) |
| POST /import/execute | customer:create | N/A |
| GET /import/jobs | customer:read | OWN (SALES_REP), TEAM (SALES_MANAGER), ALL (CRM_ADMIN+) |
| GET /import/jobs/{id} | customer:read | OWN/TEAM/ALL per role |

### Input Validation
- File upload: whitelist CSV extension, scan for malicious content
- CSV parsing: sanitize input to prevent CSV injection
- Rate limiting: Max 5 uploads per user per hour

### Data Protection
- Mask sensitive fields (email, phone) in error reports for AUDITOR role
- Delete uploaded files after 7 days
```

